            Library Accounts
          Heading link



 
Copy link









                            UIC Library account
                    

                Request and renew physical books and media from UIC and I-Share libraries.
            









                            Interlibrary loan account
                    

                Request articles and items not available through I-Share
            










            Details
          Heading link



 
Copy link



Set up an account
You can set up a Library account with your NetID or your iCard.
Trouble logging in?

Sometimes it helps to logout your UIC account, then try again.
Try resetting your browser cache and cookies.
If you’re still having trouble, please contact us.







            Help
          Heading link



 
Copy link









                            Set up a library account
                    

                Thursday, June 10, 2021
            

                UIC students, faculty and staff have automatic access to UIC Library resources. Alumni and visitors can apply for borrowing cards.
            









                            Get help with writing, style and citations
                    

                Thursday, June 10, 2021
            

                The UIC Library has resources to help you with writing, style and citations.
            









                            How to Search
                    

                Thursday, June 10, 2021
            

                You can search for articles, books, news, events and more from the Library homepage and the magnifying glass icon on the top right of every page.
            







